[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Turns teleport stones into a fast-travel system that reaches every place you've been, with no cooldown and an optional immersive fee.[/size]

[size=3][b]Core[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Press Z (rebindable)[/b] or RB on a controller to open the teleport menu — provided you have at least one teleport stone in your inventory. If you rebind and type something the game can't parse, the mod silently reverts to the default key.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zero cooldown[/b] — vanilla locks the teleport stone for a few minutes after each use. That's permanently removed.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Every discovered zone[/b] appears in the menu — not just the hardcoded game destinations. This includes mines, the mill, the village farmer, the lighthouse, the refugee camp, the tavern, etc.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Unlocking locations[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Visit the zone once[/b] — it then appears in the menu. The mod doesn't gate anything that vanilla hasn't already revealed to you.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]A few zones also need an NPC conversation[/b] before they appear — the Mill and the Farmer require talking to their respective NPC first (same rule vanilla applies to discovering them on the world map).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Custom teleport points[/b] — save the player's current position to a slot with a configurable keybind, then jump back to that exact coordinate later. Slots persist across saves. Useful for bookmarking a specific stockpile, crafting area, or dungeon entrance.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Gerry the ferryman[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Fee[/b] — Gerry collects around 1% of your current money per teleport, capped at a maximum of 5%. It's a small drag on wealth, not a progress blocker.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Disable Gerry or his fee[/b] if you'd prefer the UI without the character, or no cost at all. Each is a separate toggle.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]UI options[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Rollout speed[/b] — speed up the menu animation if you're teleporting often.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Locations per page[/b] — configurable. Larger values show more zones without paging but make the menu taller.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Sort alphabetically[/b] — off by default (game-order), on puts zones in A-Z order.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Previous-page choice memory[/b] — when you page back, the cursor remembers where you were.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Cinematic teleport effect[/b] — vanilla shows a short animation when you warp. Toggle off for instant cuts.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory across every zone. Pairs perfectly with multi-zone teleporting.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] — teleport drops to stockpiles automatically. Combine for a supply-chain you never have to touch.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/60]I Build Where I Want[/url] — build anywhere, then warp back to it later.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/53]Longer Days[/url] — more hours per day to spend teleporting between projects.[/size]
[/list]

